# SuperGit Project

VS Code extension for a Git commit graph and branch tracking webview.

## Source of truth

- Product behavior/UI: read all files in `Design/` before UI or behavior changes.
- Spec: `Design/git-graph-extension-spec.md`
- Visual reference: `Design/git-graph-extension-ui-v2.jsx`
- Assets: `assets/icon.png` (package/panel icon), `assets/logo.png` (webview logo)

## Design goals

- Dark VS Code-native webview; dense, operational, tool-like UI (not a landing page)
- Commit graph tab, branch tracking tab, multi-remote visibility, guarded Git actions
- Stable dimensions for graph lanes, sidebars, toolbar, rows, status areas
- Do not replace real UI with explanatory placeholder text
- Branch tracking actions must be **contextual**: after selection, show ahead/behind/synced/diverged/no-upstream and enable/highlight only sensible push/pull/upstream actions

